```php
<?php
$json = '{"name":"Alice","age":30,"hobbies":["reading","hiking"]}';

// Decode to associative array (second parameter true)
$array = json_decode($json, true);
print_r($array);

// Decode to object
$obj = json_decode($json);
echo $obj->name; // Alice
?>
```

## Check for Errors

If JSON is invalid, `json_decode()` returns null. Use `json_last_error()` to get the error code and `json_last_error_msg()` for the message.

```php
$data = json_decode($invalidJson);
if (json_last_error() !== JSON_ERROR_NONE) {
    echo 'JSON error: ' . json_last_error_msg();
}
```
